        "text": ":loudspeaker: *Upcoming R-Ladies Rome Event*\n\nWe’re excited to welcome *Isabella Velásquez (Developer Relations at Posit PBC)* for our next talk:\n\n*What’s New in {dplyr} 1.2.0*\n\nIf you work with the tidyverse, this session will walk through the latest updates in *{dplyr}* and help you understand when to use the new features in real workflows.\n\nWe’ll cover:\n• new when_any() and when_all() helpers\n• alternatives to case_match()\n• improvements to filtering and data transformation\n• practical examples you can apply immediately\n\n:date: Date: March 18, 2026\n:clock6: Time: 6pm CET\n:link: Register here: <https:\/\/www.meetup.com\/rladies-rome\/events\/313630747>\n\nWhether you’re new to R or an experienced user, this will be a practical tour of what’s new in dplyr.\n\nHope to see some of you there! :rocket:",
